column5: A couple little ones I wheeled this past weekend ... Nothin' too crazy! lol, but, hopefully this summer Ill be able to wheel some 5+lbs bass.  Caught on Lake Nepewassi, both using jitterbug(green on black), sun was JUST setting behind the trees, about 5 feet of water ... Love the weed beds on Nepewassi, produce such nice fish .. and ridiculously small pike
nice fish trevor. ahh the jitter bug

Awesome! Thanks for the report dude! I grew up fishing nep for bass and walleye.... And saw my first ever musky caught in that lake! I'd love to get my kids out on that lake again someday!  Cheers, Ryan
Its a start! Top water fish are fun to catch, big or small. thanks for sharing.
